OL,3,CCall for fair, ambitious climate plan
OL,4,Cas UK emissions-cutting targets at risk
OL,6,FAfter a campaign led by Friends of the
OL,7,FEarth, the Climate Change Act became
OL,8,Flaw in November 2008 with near-
OL,9,Funanimous cross-party political
OL,10,Fsupport, requiring the UK to cut its
OL,11,Femissions by 80% by 2050, which has
OL,12,Fnow been updated to 100% or net zero.
OL,14,FThe Friends of the Earth report shows
OL,15,Fthat, in the 15 years from the Act
OL,16,Fbecoming law to 2023, emissions have
OL,17,Ffallen 41%, compared with only 16% in
OL,18,Fthe 15 years before the law was passed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
